257
00:22:59,804 --> 00:23:02,204
I invited him over.
Why?

258
00:23:02,324 --> 00:23:03,684
What's the matter, Charley?

259
00:23:03,804 --> 00:23:07,124
Afraid I'd never come over
without being invited first?

260
00:23:08,084 --> 00:23:09,684
You're quite right.

261
00:23:09,805 --> 00:23:12,084
Of course, now that
I've been made welcome...

262
00:23:12,204 --> 00:23:15,005
I'll probably drop by
quite a bit.

263
00:23:15,125 --> 00:23:18,005
In fact,
anytime I feel like it.

264
00:23:20,205 --> 00:23:23,004
With your mother's
kind permission, of course.

265
00:23:23,124 --> 00:23:25,285
Oh, jerry, anytime.

266
00:23:27,004 --> 00:23:30,804
It's nice that someone interesting has
finally moved into the neighbourhood.

267
00:23:33,004 --> 00:23:34,885
Charley, are you all right?

268
00:23:36,805 --> 00:23:38,804
Yeah, Mom, I'm fine.

269
00:23:40,324 --> 00:23:42,484
I just gotta get back
to my trig.

270
00:23:42,604 --> 00:23:44,085
Nice to meet you.

271
00:23:45,405 --> 00:23:47,284
See you.

272
00:23:47,404 --> 00:23:49,005
Soon.

273
00:27:16,885 --> 00:27:19,125
We wouldn't want towake
your mother, would we?

274
00:27:20,405 --> 00:27:23,006
Then I'd have to kill her too.

275
00:27:23,126 --> 00:27:24,605
Right?

276
00:27:48,805 --> 00:27:52,325
Do you realize how much trouble
you've caused me?

277
00:27:52,405 --> 00:27:54,485
Spying on me.

278
00:27:54,605 --> 00:27:57,406
Almost disturbing my sleep
this afternoon.

279
00:27:58,885 --> 00:28:00,805
Telling policemen about me!

280
00:28:11,406 --> 00:28:13,925
You deserve to die, boy.

281
00:28:18,006 --> 00:28:21,806
Of course, I could give you
something I don't have.

282
00:28:21,925 --> 00:28:23,285
A choice.

283
00:28:24,605 --> 00:28:26,725
Forget about me, Charley.

284
00:28:27,805 --> 00:28:30,005
Forget about me,
and I'll forget about you.

285
00:28:30,085 --> 00:28:31,925
What do you say, Charley?

286
00:28:44,206 --> 00:28:45,526
Fool.

287
00:30:02,326 --> 00:30:03,686
Charley!

288
00:30:18,086 --> 00:30:20,406
Charley, can you hear me?

289
00:30:27,806 --> 00:30:29,206
Charley, is thatyou?

290
00:30:30,486 --> 00:30:32,006
My door is stuck

291
00:30:42,806 --> 00:30:46,206
- What is going on?
- Nothing. I just had a nightmare.

292
00:30:47,406 --> 00:30:50,486
I had one last night.
It was awful.

293
00:30:50,606 --> 00:30:54,606
I was at this white sale
and suddenly realized I was stark naked.

294
00:30:55,606 --> 00:30:57,526
- Now what is it?
- Nothing.

295
00:30:57,606 --> 00:30:59,406
Just raccoons
in the garbage again.

296
00:30:59,526 --> 00:31:01,925
- Go back to sleep.
- But what about your nightmare?

297
00:31:02,006 --> 00:31:04,486
- Do you want a Valium?
- I'm fine now.

298
00:31:04,606 --> 00:31:07,005
- Honest.
- I do need my sleep.

299
00:31:07,126 --> 00:31:10,726
I start the night shift tomorrow.
3:00 in the morning.

300
00:31:10,806 --> 00:31:13,606
- It's so bad for my complexion.
- Good night, Mom.

301
00:32:02,606 --> 00:32:04,726
I know you're there, Charley.

302
00:32:04,806 --> 00:32:06,406
I can see you.

303
00:32:15,686 --> 00:32:17,406
What's the matter, Charley?

304
00:32:17,526 --> 00:32:19,286
scared?

305
00:32:20,406 --> 00:32:24,006
You started this, Charley,
and I'm gonna finish it.

306
00:32:27,206 --> 00:32:29,287
I just destroyed your car,
Charley.

307
00:32:30,886 --> 00:32:34,206
But that's nothing compared
to what I'm gonna do to you...

308
00:32:36,606 --> 00:32:37,927
tomorrow night.

309
00:32:44,486 --> 00:32:46,606
Once again, your host...

310
00:32:46,726 --> 00:32:48,406
Peter Vincent.

311
00:32:48,487 --> 00:32:50,807
Good evening, horror fans.

312
00:32:50,886 --> 00:32:53,806
Did you know
there are a lot of people...

313
00:32:53,926 --> 00:32:56,326
who do not believe in vampires?

314
00:32:57,206 --> 00:32:58,606
But I do...

315
00:32:58,726 --> 00:33:02,327
because I know they exist.

316
00:33:02,406 --> 00:33:07,127
I have fought them
in all their guises--

317
00:33:07,206 --> 00:33:10,886
man, wolves, bats--

318
00:33:11,006 --> 00:33:15,286
and I have always won!

319
00:33:16,206 --> 00:33:18,606
That is why they call me...

320
00:33:18,726 --> 00:33:21,127
the great vampire killer.

321
00:33:22,887 --> 00:33:24,326
Now...

322
00:33:25,527 --> 00:33:27,526
watch me do it.

323
00:33:36,806 --> 00:33:38,086
Go, Peter.

324
00:33:43,006 --> 00:33:44,727
Go.

325
00:33:55,606 --> 00:33:59,527
Mr Vincent,
could I talk to you for a minute?

326
00:33:59,606 --> 00:34:02,206
Please, Mr Vincent.
It's very, very important.

327
00:34:02,326 --> 00:34:05,527
- What do you want me to sign?
- Pardon me?

328
00:34:05,606 --> 00:34:07,526
You do want my autograph,
don't you?

329
00:34:08,606 --> 00:34:11,806
No, sir, I was curious about
what you said last night on TV...

330
00:34:11,887 --> 00:34:13,686
about believing in vampires.

331
00:34:13,807 --> 00:34:15,606
What about it?

332
00:34:15,687 --> 00:34:17,207
Were you serious?

333
00:34:18,007 --> 00:34:19,407
Oh, absolutely.

334
00:34:21,207 --> 00:34:23,886
Unfortunately,
none of your generation seems to be.

335
00:34:24,006 --> 00:34:25,407
What do you mean?

336
00:34:25,526 --> 00:34:29,127
I have just been fired because nobody
wants to see vampire killers any more...

337
00:34:29,206 --> 00:34:30,726
or vampires either.

338
00:34:30,807 --> 00:34:33,527
Apparently all they want
are demented madmen...

339
00:34:33,606 --> 00:34:37,127
running around in ski masks
hacking up young virgins.

340
00:34:37,207 --> 00:34:38,487
Excuse me.

341
00:34:40,206 --> 00:34:42,007
I believe in vampires.

342
00:34:47,887 --> 00:34:49,127
That's nice.

343
00:34:50,407 --> 00:34:54,006
If only there had been more of you,
perhaps my ratings would've been higher.

344
00:34:54,127 --> 00:34:57,687
In fact, I have one
living next door to me.

345
00:34:57,807 --> 00:34:59,607
Would you help me kill him?

346
00:35:02,327 --> 00:35:03,606
Pardon me?

347
00:35:03,687 --> 00:35:06,127
You know that murder
a few days ago?

348
00:35:06,207 --> 00:35:07,687
Yes.

349
00:35:07,807 --> 00:35:11,807
The guy who lives next door to me
did it, and he's a vampire.

350
00:35:13,527 --> 00:35:17,206
If this is your idea of a joke,
I am not amused.

351
00:35:17,287 --> 00:35:19,287
Mr Vincent, I am not joking.

352
00:35:19,406 --> 00:35:21,527
I am deadly serious.

353
00:35:22,607 --> 00:35:25,407
Well, if you would excuse me--

354
00:35:26,487 --> 00:35:29,406
But, Mr Vincent,
you have to believe me.

355
00:35:29,526 --> 00:35:33,207
I'm telling the truth.
You just said you believed in vampires.

356
00:35:33,287 --> 00:35:35,286
I lied.

357
00:35:35,407 --> 00:35:37,287
Now, if you will leave me alone--

358
00:35:37,407 --> 00:35:39,207
You have to listen to me!

359
00:35:39,286 --> 00:35:41,687
The vampire tried
to kill me last night...

360
00:35:41,807 --> 00:35:43,887
and trashed my car
when he didn't succeed.

361
00:35:44,007 --> 00:35:48,807
He's gonna be back tonight.
If I don't get help, he's gonna kill me.

362
00:35:48,886 --> 00:35:50,727
Mr Vincent!

363
00:35:50,806 --> 00:35:53,207
Just listen to me for a second.

364
00:35:53,287 --> 00:35:54,727
No! Wait!

365
00:35:54,807 --> 00:35:56,887
Please, Mr Vincent!
Wait!

366
00:36:03,006 --> 00:36:06,407
- What are you doing here?
- What about you? You just dumped him.

367
00:36:06,487 --> 00:36:09,887
- It's none of your business.
- So you do like him.

368
00:36:10,006 --> 00:36:11,407
Anybody home?

369
00:36:19,687 --> 00:36:21,287
Wow.

370
00:36:27,207 --> 00:36:29,127
What's all this for?

371
00:36:29,207 --> 00:36:31,207
Self-defence.

372
00:36:31,287 --> 00:36:33,407
Not that I think I'll need it.

373
00:36:33,527 --> 00:36:35,287
He'll be dead before nightfall.

374
00:36:35,407 --> 00:36:37,887
- Who will be?
- Dandrige.

375
00:36:38,007 --> 00:36:41,687
I'm waiting for the guy he liveswith to
leave, then I'm gonna find his coffin...

376
00:36:41,807 --> 00:36:43,687
and pound this
through his heart.

377
00:36:45,207 --> 00:36:46,727
That's murder, Charley.

378
00:36:49,007 --> 00:36:51,527
You can't murder a vampire, Amy.

379
00:36:51,607 --> 00:36:54,127
They're dead. Remember?

380
00:36:56,207 --> 00:36:59,007
Listen.
I just taped this.

381
00:37:02,407 --> 00:37:04,327
Amy.

382
00:37:04,407 --> 00:37:06,207
What are we gonna do?

383
00:37:06,327 --> 00:37:08,327
This is just like Fright Night.

384
00:37:08,407 --> 00:37:12,327
Nowforthe news. Anotheryoung woman's
body was discovered this morning...

385
00:37:12,407 --> 00:37:14,207
in back of the sheridan Mall--

386
00:37:14,327 --> 00:37:15,887
I don't have any choice.

387
00:37:16,887 --> 00:37:18,887
Somebody has to stop him.

388
00:37:20,607 --> 00:37:23,407
It's gonna be dangerous
going into that house all alone.

389
00:37:26,207 --> 00:37:28,607
You'll need all the help
you can get.

390
00:37:29,287 --> 00:37:31,607
Somebody like Peter Vincent,
for instance?

391
00:37:31,687 --> 00:37:33,127
I tried him already.

392
00:37:34,207 --> 00:37:36,887
Well, let us try again
before you do anything.

393
00:37:37,007 --> 00:37:39,408
There's not enough time, Amy.

394
00:37:39,527 --> 00:37:42,327
Well, what happens
if you go into that house alone...

395
00:37:42,407 --> 00:37:44,127
and he gets you?

396
00:37:44,208 --> 00:37:46,007
Who's gonna stop him then?

397
00:37:46,128 --> 00:37:50,207
Yeah. Then he'll be able to suck his way
through the entire town.

398
00:37:51,527 --> 00:37:53,887
Not that it would be
much of a loss.

399
00:37:54,007 --> 00:37:56,327
Charley, it's gonna be dark soon.

400
00:37:57,887 --> 00:38:00,727
You don't want to go
into that house then, doyou?

401
00:38:00,808 --> 00:38:03,128
No, you're right there.

402
00:38:07,407 --> 00:38:10,007
- All right, try him again.
- Great.

403
00:38:10,007 --> 00:38:13,288
You promise you're not gonna
do anything till you hear from us?

404
00:38:15,807 --> 00:38:17,128
Okay. Come on.

405
00:38:19,887 --> 00:38:22,007
You don't believe me,
doyou?

406
00:38:23,687 --> 00:38:25,407
I love you, Charley.

407
00:38:25,527 --> 00:38:26,887
Hey, Amy, come on!

408
00:38:44,727 --> 00:38:45,807
Yes?

409
00:38:45,887 --> 00:38:48,808
Mr. Vincent,
could we talk to you for a moment?

410
00:38:48,887 --> 00:38:51,688
I'm afraid now
is not the best time.

411
00:38:51,808 --> 00:38:54,487
Please.
It's very important.

412
00:38:57,807 --> 00:38:59,407
Well, if you would just...

413
00:38:59,527 --> 00:39:02,327
wait there for one moment--

414
00:39:03,687 --> 00:39:04,887
Come in!

415
00:39:07,687 --> 00:39:10,007
What can I do for you?

416
00:39:11,408 --> 00:39:12,808
An autograph, perhaps?

417
00:39:14,407 --> 00:39:17,287
Perhaps an interview
for your school newspaper?

418
00:39:17,407 --> 00:39:19,528
I'm afraid this is
much more important.

419
00:39:21,127 --> 00:39:22,487
Really?

420
00:39:24,608 --> 00:39:27,527
What could be more important
than my autograph?

421
00:39:27,608 --> 00:39:29,207
Saving a boy's life.

422
00:39:30,007 --> 00:39:31,527
Oh. Yes.

423
00:39:31,608 --> 00:39:35,288
I can see where that
could be more important.

424
00:39:35,408 --> 00:39:39,528
Perhaps you would care to explain.

425
00:39:40,727 --> 00:39:43,528
Remember a fruitcake kid
named Charley Brewster?

426
00:39:43,607 --> 00:39:44,888
He said he saw you.

427
00:39:46,327 --> 00:39:48,888
The one who believes
a vampire lives next to him.

428
00:39:49,008 --> 00:39:51,687
Oh, yes.
You know, he is insane.

429
00:39:53,128 --> 00:39:54,888
Oh, my dear...

430
00:39:55,008 --> 00:39:57,407
I do hope he's not
a friend of yours.

431
00:39:57,528 --> 00:40:00,488
Yeah, she's got the hots
for the creep.

432
00:40:00,607 --> 00:40:01,888
Amy!

433
00:40:02,008 --> 00:40:04,127
We need your help to stop him.

434
00:40:04,208 --> 00:40:06,887
He really believes
his next-door neighbour is a vampire...

435
00:40:07,007 --> 00:40:08,888
and he's planning to kill him.

436
00:40:09,008 --> 00:40:11,287
With a stake through the heart.

437
00:40:13,808 --> 00:40:15,687
Are you two serious?

438
00:40:16,887 --> 00:40:18,208
Oh, my dear.

439
00:40:18,328 --> 00:40:21,608
Your friend needs a psychiatrist,
not a vampire killer.

440
00:40:21,687 --> 00:40:24,208
- Please, Mr Vincent.
- I'm afraid not.

441
00:40:24,327 --> 00:40:27,288
You see, Hollywood beckons.

442
00:40:27,408 --> 00:40:31,688
I have just been offered
a starring role in a major film.

443
00:40:31,808 --> 00:40:34,727
I have even had to quit
Fright Night.

444
00:40:34,808 --> 00:40:36,807
- I'll give you money.
- How much?

445
00:40:36,888 --> 00:40:38,808
I have a $500 savings bond.

446
00:40:38,888 --> 00:40:40,128
I'll take it.

447
00:40:41,808 --> 00:40:47,207
Now, how are we going to cure
your little friend...

448
00:40:47,288 --> 00:40:49,127
ofthis delusion?

449
00:40:49,807 --> 00:40:51,688
I got it all figured out.

450
00:40:51,808 --> 00:40:54,128
We all go next door
to the neighbour...

451
00:40:54,207 --> 00:40:57,207
and you perform some kind of
vampire test on him...

452
00:40:57,288 --> 00:40:59,287
to pronounce him human.

453
00:40:59,407 --> 00:41:02,808
You know.
Like in Orgy of the Damned?

454
00:41:02,888 --> 00:41:05,688
Where you looked in the mirror...

455
00:41:05,808 --> 00:41:10,488
the guy didn't have a reflection,
so then you knew he was a vampire.

456
00:41:11,608 --> 00:41:13,008
Oh, yes.

457
00:41:15,408 --> 00:41:17,808
That was one
of my favourite roles.

458
00:41:21,288 --> 00:41:23,808
Do you know...

459
00:41:23,888 --> 00:41:25,688
I still...

460
00:41:26,808 --> 00:41:28,608
have the prop.

461
00:41:59,408 --> 00:42:00,488
It's for you.

462
00:42:07,528 --> 00:42:09,288
Yes, this is jerry Dandrige.

463
00:42:12,488 --> 00:42:14,808
I see.

464
00:42:14,888 --> 00:42:16,208
Well, yes, of course.

465
00:42:16,328 --> 00:42:19,288
I'm always willing
to help young people...

466
00:42:19,408 --> 00:42:22,408
but I'm afraid that crosses
are out ofthe question.

467
00:42:22,488 --> 00:42:26,408
You see,
I've been reborn recently.

468
00:42:26,488 --> 00:42:28,328
He's a reborn Christian.

469
00:42:28,408 --> 00:42:30,728
He thinks crosses
would be sacrilegious.

470
00:42:30,808 --> 00:42:34,729
- Ask him how he feels about holy water.
- How about holy water?

471
00:42:34,808 --> 00:42:36,128
No. Won't do either.

472
00:42:36,208 --> 00:42:39,688
Tell him it's ordinary tap water.
All he has to do is sip it.

473
00:42:43,288 --> 00:42:45,888
Oh, yes. Yes. Okay.
That sounds fine.

474
00:42:46,008 --> 00:42:50,208
But don't bring him over
until 6:00 tomorrow.

475
00:42:50,328 --> 00:42:52,328
I'll be out until then.

476
00:42:55,888 --> 00:42:58,888
Seems we don't have to go out
tonight after all.

477
00:42:59,008 --> 00:43:03,128
His friends are bringing him over
tomorrow night...

478
00:43:03,208 --> 00:43:05,288
to prove to him that I'm not...

479
00:43:06,328 --> 00:43:07,688
a vampire.

480
00:43:12,128 --> 00:43:14,888
It's 6:10. He said
he was gonna be here at 6:00.

481
00:43:15,008 --> 00:43:17,288
He said he'd be here.
He'll be here.

482
00:43:18,329 --> 00:43:19,688
Here he comes!

483
00:43:26,128 --> 00:43:28,889
Thank you.
Charley Brewster, I presume.

484
00:43:29,008 --> 00:43:30,888
Peter Vincent, vampire killer.

485
00:43:31,008 --> 00:43:34,008
I cannot tell you
how much I appreciate this.

486
00:43:34,128 --> 00:43:35,889
Good evening.
Now, down to business.

487
00:43:36,008 --> 00:43:40,208
Where is the lair of the suspected
creature ofthe night?

488
00:43:40,328 --> 00:43:41,288
There.

489
00:43:43,208 --> 00:43:45,008
Oh, yes.
I see what you mean.

490
00:43:46,088 --> 00:43:49,008
There is
a distinct possibility.

491
00:43:50,208 --> 00:43:52,089
Now, shall we go?

492
00:43:52,209 --> 00:43:54,488
Wait.
Where's your stakes and hammers?

493
00:43:54,608 --> 00:43:56,488
I left them in my bag.

494
00:43:56,609 --> 00:43:58,408
You're not going in there
without them.

495
00:43:58,488 --> 00:44:02,609
But I have to prove that he is a vampire
before I kill him, Charley.

496
00:44:02,728 --> 00:44:05,288
Look, I know he's a vampire!

497
00:44:05,408 --> 00:44:08,208
I am the one
who has to know, Charley.

498
00:44:08,328 --> 00:44:10,088
How are you gonna do that?

499
00:44:11,009 --> 00:44:12,489
This is holy water.

500
00:44:12,608 --> 00:44:15,008
If a drop touches him,
he will blister.

501
00:44:15,129 --> 00:44:17,289
I have asked him to drink it...

502
00:44:17,408 --> 00:44:20,008
while we all watch.

503
00:44:20,088 --> 00:44:21,529
He readily agreed.

504
00:44:21,608 --> 00:44:24,888
But if I'm right and you prove
he is a vampire...

505
00:44:25,009 --> 00:44:26,329
he'll kill us all.

506
00:44:26,408 --> 00:44:28,088
No, hewon't, Charley.

507
00:44:28,208 --> 00:44:31,208
After all, I am here to protect you,
and I am Peter Vincent!

508
00:44:31,289 --> 00:44:33,209
I know, Mr Vincent, but--

509
00:44:34,329 --> 00:44:35,689
Hey! Peter Vincent.

510
00:44:36,889 --> 00:44:38,488
Billy Cole.

511
00:44:38,608 --> 00:44:39,608
This is a pleasure.

512
00:44:40,808 --> 00:44:42,608
Won't you all come in?

513
00:44:47,609 --> 00:44:49,009
And Charley.

514
00:44:56,409 --> 00:44:59,289
Hey,jer! They're here.

515
00:45:01,128 --> 00:45:03,288
Perhaps he didn't hear you.

516
00:45:03,409 --> 00:45:05,689
He heard me, all right.

517
00:45:26,208 --> 00:45:27,288
Mr Vincent.

