the door down.

781
01:22:37,478 --> 01:22:39,477
You make as much noise
asyou can.

782
01:22:41,478 --> 01:22:43,798
Help!

783
01:22:43,877 --> 01:22:45,878
Let me out!

784
01:22:47,317 --> 01:22:50,918
Please! Open the door!
Help! Somebody!

785
01:22:50,998 --> 01:22:54,278
I think she just opened her eyes.

786
01:23:00,197 --> 01:23:01,997
All right. Grab her.
Let's get out ofhere.

787
01:23:02,117 --> 01:23:04,398
We can't. Look

788
01:23:08,198 --> 01:23:09,797
Oh, my God.

789
01:23:12,518 --> 01:23:14,278
Something wrong?

790
01:23:14,398 --> 01:23:17,798
Yes. We have a visitor.

791
01:23:19,397 --> 01:23:21,718
Is it too late to save her?

792
01:23:21,798 --> 01:23:23,078
No.

793
01:23:24,278 --> 01:23:27,077
Not if we kill Dandrige
before dawn.

794
01:23:28,197 --> 01:23:29,798
Are you sure?

795
01:23:29,878 --> 01:23:32,198
So far, everything has been
like it was in movies.

796
01:23:32,278 --> 01:23:34,918
Now we just have to keep hoping.

797
01:23:37,798 --> 01:23:39,598
Let's go.

798
01:23:53,198 --> 01:23:55,998
Well, what do we have here?

799
01:23:57,878 --> 01:23:59,717
Vampire killers?

800
01:24:03,998 --> 01:24:05,398
Stop or I'll shoot.

801
01:24:07,398 --> 01:24:08,598
I mean it.

802
01:24:08,678 --> 01:24:10,598
Don't force me to shoot.

803
01:24:22,798 --> 01:24:23,798
Stop!

804
01:24:26,598 --> 01:24:28,118
We have him.

805
01:24:31,478 --> 01:24:33,398
Do you?

806
01:24:37,798 --> 01:24:39,718
What did he mean by that?

807
01:24:40,678 --> 01:24:43,198
Nothing.
He was just bluffing.

808
01:26:44,118 --> 01:26:45,399
She's worse!

809
01:26:45,478 --> 01:26:47,879
Come on.
We're running out oftime.

810
01:27:00,678 --> 01:27:02,519
Amy.

811
01:27:03,798 --> 01:27:05,119
Awake.

812
01:27:06,598 --> 01:27:09,478
I command you...

813
01:27:09,598 --> 01:27:13,318
to awake!

814
01:27:19,799 --> 01:27:24,599
Show me how much
you love me, Amy.

815
01:27:25,599 --> 01:27:27,999
Kill them...

816
01:27:29,119 --> 01:27:30,678
both!

817
01:27:37,799 --> 01:27:39,478
He's on the roof.

818
01:27:39,598 --> 01:27:41,398
I'm going up there.

819
01:28:11,199 --> 01:28:13,319
He's not up here.

820
01:28:13,399 --> 01:28:15,199
Look out!

821
01:28:17,598 --> 01:28:19,479
He's going downstairs.

822
01:28:32,398 --> 01:28:35,479
So.

823
01:28:47,799 --> 01:28:48,998
Stay back

824
01:28:53,999 --> 01:28:55,199
Back

825
01:29:06,119 --> 01:29:09,718
You have to have faith
for that to work..

826
01:29:09,799 --> 01:29:12,879
Mr Vincent!

827
01:29:12,998 --> 01:29:15,119
Remember?

828
01:29:56,599 --> 01:30:01,599
You're out oftime,
Mr Dandrige.

829
01:30:01,719 --> 01:30:03,719
Look overyour shoulder.

830
01:30:16,199 --> 01:30:17,479
Back!

831
01:30:56,879 --> 01:30:59,479
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. Quick He's in the basement.

832
01:31:09,879 --> 01:31:12,600
Quick his coffin has got to be
down here somewhere.

833
01:31:30,599 --> 01:31:31,999
What was that?

834
01:31:32,119 --> 01:31:34,680
You keep searching.
I'll check it out.

835
01:31:51,120 --> 01:31:52,679
Amy?

836
01:31:52,799 --> 01:31:54,800
It's me.

837
01:31:54,879 --> 01:31:56,119
I know.

838
01:32:15,719 --> 01:32:17,119
I found it.

839
01:32:18,999 --> 01:32:20,880
Don't be frightened, Charley.

840
01:32:21,000 --> 01:32:22,680
Hurry. Get it open!

841
01:32:22,800 --> 01:32:24,200
He's locked it
from the inside.

842
01:32:25,800 --> 01:32:27,119
What's wrong?

843
01:32:29,599 --> 01:32:32,879
Don't you want me any more?

844
01:32:39,199 --> 01:32:42,280
It's not my fault, Charley.

845
01:32:42,400 --> 01:32:46,520
You promised
you wouldn't let him get me!

846
01:32:46,599 --> 01:32:48,799
You promised!

847
01:34:29,320 --> 01:34:31,000
Charley, watch out!

848
01:35:33,320 --> 01:35:35,000
Amy!

849
01:37:19,201 --> 01:37:21,720
Look! We've been
going in a circle.

850
01:37:21,801 --> 01:37:23,800
We're right back
where we started from.

851
01:37:23,881 --> 01:37:28,200
Ladies and gentlemen,
Fright Night Theatre.

852
01:37:28,281 --> 01:37:30,400
This is Peter Vincent...

853
01:37:30,520 --> 01:37:33,321
back once more with you...

854
01:37:33,400 --> 01:37:35,801
as host of Fright Night.

855
01:37:35,880 --> 01:37:40,601
I thought I'd let the vampires
rest for a little while.

856
01:37:43,201 --> 01:37:44,601
Right, Charley?

857
01:37:46,121 --> 01:37:50,120
Tonight, the threat comes
not from beyond the grave...

858
01:37:50,201 --> 01:37:53,081
but from beyond the stars...

859
01:37:53,201 --> 01:37:57,201
as alien beings stalk
an unwary summer camp...

860
01:37:57,321 --> 01:38:00,921
in Mars Wants Flesh.

861
01:38:01,001 --> 01:38:03,881
I do not star in it.

862
01:38:25,601 --> 01:38:27,000
Is something wrong?

863
01:38:32,001 --> 01:38:33,880
Nothing.

864
01:38:52,000 --> 01:38:54,681
Oh, you're so cool, Brewster!


